Use Godot's OS.get_name() to detect the platform and DisplayServer.screen_get_size() to get the current screen resolution. Then, set the window size using OS.window_size property or via ProjectSettings at runtime. Save a flag (e.g., in user://) to ensure this setting only occurs on first launch. Example:

func _ready():
    var platform = OS.get_name()
    var screen_size = DisplayServer.screen_get_size(0)
    OS.window_size = screen_size
    OS.window_fullscreen = true
    # Save setting/flag to prevent re-configuration next time

Use ProjectSettings.set_setting("display/window/size/viewport_width", screen_size.x) and similarly for height if needed, but note these changes affect only current session unless saved. Refer to Godot docs on OS and DisplayServer for details.

